&lt;p&gt;This is a note about the integration of the Certbot with Let&amp;rsquo;s encrypt DNS&amp;ndash;01 authentication mechanism. Will not use any cloud services (fuck cloud), just self-hosted DNS instances, like good old times. I&amp;rsquo;ll show how to configure Knot DNS to accept dynamic DNS updates from &lt;code&gt;knsupdate&lt;/code&gt; and how to create a rudimentary hook for Certbot which will use &lt;code&gt;knsupdate&lt;/code&gt; to set &lt;code&gt;TXT&lt;/code&gt; records with &lt;code&gt;_acme-challenge&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://corpix.dev/2022/02/using-certbot-with-knot-dns-knsupdate.html?utm_source=certbot&amp;amp;utm_medium=Atom"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content></entry></feed>